Ireland plans to use profits from
companies in which it owns stakes, such as EBS and Bord Gais, to
fund new infrastructure and job creation programs, the  Sunday
Business Post  reported.  The plan will require the support of the European Union,
 European Central Bank  and the  International Monetary Fund , the
Dublin-based newspaper said, without saying where it got the
information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
